<paragraph blockId="216.[151,1437,1590,2014]" lastBlockId="217.[199,1436,150,249]" lastPageId="217" lastPageNumber="218" pageId="216" pageNumber="217">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[265,508,1951,1977]" pageId="216" pageNumber="217" pagination="199 - 256" refId="ref369841" refString="Rondani, C. (1868 c) Sciomyzinae italicae collectae, distinctae et in ordinem dispositae. Dipterol. ital. Prodromi. Pars VII, fasc. II. Dipterorum stirps XIX. Sciomyzinae Rndn. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 11 (2), 199 - 256." type="journal article" year="1868">Rondani (1868c: 228)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1868" box="[627,853,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Sciomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="216" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="majuscula">
<emphasis box="[627,853,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="216" pageNumber="217">Sciomyza majuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single male: “ 
<emphasis box="[1090,1305,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="216" pageNumber="217">Marem unicum legi</emphasis>
[I collected a single male]”. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Rivosecchi, L." box="[539,791,1987,2014]" pageId="216" pageNumber="217" pagination="45 - 50" refId="ref365613" refString="Rivosecchi, L. (1987) Note sugli Sciomyzidae. VIII. Sulla Pherbellia majuscula (Rondani, 1877) (Diptera, Acalyptera). Fragmenta Entomologica, 20 (1), 45 - 50." type="journal article" year="1987">Rivosecchi (1987: 46)</bibRefCitation>
, the MZUF specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1868" box="[1076,1316,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="216" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="majuscola">
<emphasis box="[1076,1316,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="216" pageNumber="217">Pherbellia majuscola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
numbered “1520” did not match Rondani’s description and is mislabeled, while the specimen numbered “1524”, labeled “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Fall." authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1820" box="[212,375,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Sciomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[212,318,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">Sciomyza</emphasis>
Fall.
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[381,470,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">maxima</emphasis>
n.” [manuscript name], did match it and is the 
<typeStatus box="[991,1089,187,213]" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">holotype</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1868" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="majuscola">
<emphasis box="[1134,1374,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">Pherbellia majuscola</emphasis>
Rondani, 1868
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
